caption: Of course I chose the coldest, windiest night to try Ops for the first time. Despite the sour weather, the pizza was totally worth the hype.
Delicious pizza; amazing wine list
Excellent pizza and amazing wine selections. Out of this world bottle prices
(Translated by Google) Delicious 🤤  (Original) Deliciosa 🤤

The decor of OPS is outmoded with vintage style. There is only outdoor dining available currently.  We had a salad, Marinara Pizza and Iron Age Pizza to share with a group of four. The pizza was amazingly delicious when it was served warm & fresh, especially the dough, super tender and soft.  However, since there is only outdoor seating available, the pizza is easily cooling down with tough texture in low temperature. We highly recommend to do a take out order or eat in a hurry.
Very solid pizza! Sourdough was delicious. I like the brussel sprouts 'special' they have goin on
find a friend and share the square pie. or leave the friend at home and just have one for yourself.
Otherworldly delicious pizza! Outdoor dining with heat lamps.

Upon arrival I was told my order would be ready in 5min after that passed i was told 6 more min i ended up waiting 35min in the cold instead of sitting in the car waiting because I kept being told its almost ready terrible service wouldn't recommend!!!
Best best best

Ordered a square pie... Soggy, undercooked, sauce very thin and weak, barely found any olives on the pizza, overpriced for the pizza they serve. I dont mind paying $28 for a good pizza, thats why i ordered it. But this pizza just dissapointed.
Here’s a $12 salad from Ops

Ops is the best pizza in NYC. The dough is amazing. I love the pops pizza. The natural wine is also always good, and the way there are so many options by the glass allows for the diner to try new wines all the time. Love this place. During the pandemic, the take out has also been top notch.
Delicious pizza and awesome veggie options.
I just love this place

It’s good! but not my favorite. The dough has a lot of flavor and the texture of the pizza is spot on. However they could be more generous with the topping ingredients and more varieties of flavors, especially for the price points.

I have had a terrible experience with delivery from this restaurant. Took over 2 hours. Pizza was really cold and terrible by the time it got to us. Reheating lost a lot of value because of the type of pizza. When I called to complain and inquire about the delivery I either could not get in touch or was hung up on.

I just moved to the neighborhood and ordered takeout as I heard this was the best pizza around. That is correct. I haven’t had such delicious pizza in so long and it arrived hot, with amazing doughy crust, fantastic flavorful gourmet sauce and toppings, large fresh salad w a delicious sun dried tomato vinaigrette, and flourless chocolate cake w amazing whipped cream My guests were blown away. The cheese is high quality and it arrived in a timely manner. Will order from there again in a few days:)
i dont live in ny but kool
Went here and got the salad and the square pizza. Both were excellent and I will definitely be back.
GO there immediately, eat the CALZONE, and have your life be 300% better for it.

Very very very good. Can't give it a 5 because at the end of the day, it's not roberta's or a handful of others, but 100000% worth going. I did the margarita with pepperoni. The dough is PHENOMENAL. The pepperoni was great, but they should have put more on it. For $20 it need more pepperoni. But still a great pizza! Nice staff too. They are awesome.

The best pizza I’ve had since years!! Will come back and come back and come back!! Fresh ingredients make the magic to the flavor and extremely nice service brings the comfort and casual atmosphere. Great wine selection and always option to taste before you decide for the perfect pairings. Delicious!!
super
Great spot with great pies!

Pizzas were delicious. My only complaint with them was that the mushrooms were pickled. I'd rather have fresh mushrooms on my pizza, but that's an opinion.  My biggest complaint is the drinks. We got two of the specials from the menu. We had to close our eyes and comfort each other while we tried to swallow the juices of hell one by one. A logical person would send it back, but we thought it's some long lost karma coming to get us.  But they use metal straws, so kudos for that.
This is my first time. The food is good, cozy vibes. Came here with my parents and they love it especially seafood.
Great pizza that's a little undercooked to my taste when the place is busy. Next time I'll ask for my dough to be crispy. But staff is very friendly and well dressed
Real pizza, good wine, nice atmosphere

If you are looking for snack or a place to grab a quick bit. I would definitely come here. Also, they have drinks and beers so if you need an afternoon drink, this is the place to go. But we stopped in after walking around the area. The empanadas are so good. They have meat ones and veggie ones. You cannot have an excuse to not stop in. So next time you are in the area and walking around the mission district, definitely stop in.

SO GOOD Perfect place for late night or otherwise. The seafood pizza is SO YUMMY and the margarita is heavenly. Can't make a trip to NY without visiting these guys. And at the end of the night any w ur slices go to the nearest NYPD precinct. How cute is that!??????? Great pizza, great vibes.
Great pizza and place, but they ran out of pizza dough...

Great dough if you like a strong sourdough crust. Toppings left something to be desired, both in flavor and variation on the menu— very veggie (especially onion) heavy. “Sour” beer is actually a radler (3.8% sold for $8). Very tasty but like everything else I tried on the menu, felt just slightly overpriced and oversold. Uncomfortable seating but cozy atmosphere. Give it a shot if you’re in the neighborhood, not bad.
I just got to take out delivery and was very surprised ! Great pizza, must try it you live in the neighborhood

if u r a big pizza guy and want to impress a special somebody with a special pizza....... then this is that special spot. id eat this pizza even if I was allergic to pizza because it's really really really really good. Have I made myself clear. Special pizza. Good pizza. Eat this pizza. Your welcoem
Wonderful flavors compositions that are confident, yet elegant. The dough canvas is almost perfect. Excellent service. Top 3 in the city, in my opinion. Possibly first.
Slippery floors; good pizza, good atmosphere, good service.
Awesome cozy spot for pizza and wine. You must get the calzone!
Amazing pizza. Great environment. Be prepared to wait.
It's a okay place
Great date spot
Great pizza, wine selection and atmosphere !!!

The food is good. The wait time approximation for my takeout order was off by 15 minutes. The under estimation of the wait time wasn't great, but I understand because of the business that I was witnessing as I waited.

It was an ok experience all around tbh. The pizza was small and expensive. The drinks were overpriced and they kicked us out after we finished our food even through we were still ordering drinks. They have a very very small bar and really couldn’t deviate from a limited menu. I’d rather have gone somewhere else. The ambiance inside is lovely though.
Good pizza but dirty bathrooms

Not great pizza. Soggy, overpriced, and tiny. The table set-up is not ideal either. Tiny bistro tables that don’t fit your meal. No Happy Hour, which would be good to reduce the price. Staff was lovely and the space is cute, but not functional. If you want an ok meal with great service and a nice atmosphere, this is the choice. But better pizza exists elsewhere.
cozy spot with friendly staff and great pizza. sourdough is unique and tasty. definitely recommend the square pie.

this is my fav pizza spot in nyc. the dough is made using a sourdough starter and they never refridgerate the dough. so thats the best starting point. the calzone is a must. and the salads are always solid with a nice medley of bitter greens.
Cozy place for dinner off DeKalb Ave if you are reluctant to head out to the city.

The food was perfect. You cannot beat a wood fire pizza crust. Tried both the special salad and pizza. The server picked the perfect wine for us. We tried red white and orange and were not disappointed.
Good homemade pizza and cozy atmosphere. Good for date night, not for larger parties. Tables are really small and intimate.
Wacky but fun wines with absolutely fabulous pizza.
Warmth in every aspect.

We went on a Saturday in between Lunch and Dinner crowds. The staff was very friendly and helpful. When they didn't have the wine I originally wanted our server brought over two similar wines and let me taste both to make a decision! We had the Pops pizza and the calzone special - both were amazing! The sourdough crust is delicious and they cook it perfectly.

I grew up in the pizza belt (Google it) and like anyone else who's lived in NY... I know good pizza. I also have a *thing* for going out of my way to try new food, and am in love with sourdough. So, this place is perfect. The *right size* for an intimate restaurant, and some of the best damn fired pizza I hope you ever have. Beer selection will keep most people happy and it doesn't matter, because the pizza is amazing. And the staff is super chill, too, which is a nice bonus.
Great pizza and good wines selection. The staff are amazing!!!
Beyond the delicious pizza, the salad is consistently a good choice! Also highly recommend the flourless chocolate cake as a dessert.

We went on a Friday night and waited for almost 2 hours, but I dare say it was worth it just for the bread and butter. Some of the best sourdough I’ve ever had. The pizza was impeccably fresh—we got a margherita and a pops and both were delicious. The service was great in spite of the long wait, everyone was very friendly and accommodating. Great atmosphere and great wine. I’d recommend going on a weeknight or being prepared to wait.
Great food and fast service!

Atmosphere was great and had high hopes but highly disappointed.  The service was extremely slow.  The Cicero pie showed up with 2 tomatoes and no oregano and slightly under cooked.  The square pie had luke warm sauce. Stick with Roberta’s nearby.
great wine list. great pizza

Over priced and dirty. The pizza had the crust burnt. The service was non friendly and we had to wait 30 min in total after ordering in advance for a pickup. It was ridiculous for the size we got to wait 30-35 min. There was no sense of order as to who was  taking orders or someone who could at the very least  help you the minute you walk in. You sort of come in feeling lost and confused. Not professional and definitely not worth the price. This was a complete mistake to walk into.
We come here all the time for amazing pizza, calzones and natural wine. Everything we have had has been incredible. The service is top notch as well, everyone is super friendly and knowledgeable.
Beautiful space, great pizza, salad, and wine list. Love.

Really surprised at all the positive reviews here. We ordered the square pizza which was $28. After all the great reviews and a big price tag, I was expecting something worthwhile. The pizza was marginally better than something we could have done at home. It appears to even be using some kind of store bought shredded cheese. Honestly, the square pizza is an oversized bagel bite.  We also got the salad. This is large, whole lettuce leaves with dressing ladled on top. Like soup poured into lettuce cups.  Service was attentive but lots of attitude. There must have been 10 employees there with the same number of diners. Seemed like a lot of them were there to eat the employee dinner which looked 10x better than what they served us.

Ok so the gf and myself were looking for a Naples style pizza in NYC. We searched the web and this was a convenient distance away from where we live that didn't require us to drive into the city. We had the margherita pie with pepperoni and the calzone. The calzone was flavorful 👍. The margherita though was not what what we were hoping for. We set our expectations too high due to our experience in Naples. The pizza wasn't horrible but wasn't great either. The best part of it was the bread. The staff was friendly but in my opinion the wait isn't worth it. Also there was no mozzarella on our pie.
Love the waitress
Best pizza in Brooklyn. Yes, way better that Robertas.

A glass in my salad. It is all I can say. a crystal that luckily I didn't chew or swallow. And as if this was not enough, the manager was very rude and condescending. He tried to make me beleive that it was not a piece of glass but a piece of salt. I insisted no, it was crystal. He took it from my hands and touched it and then accepted that it was a piece of glass. but he questioned me until the end, until he touched it himself.

Fermentation of the dough makes this pizza really stand out. Great flavor and texture to the crust. Pizza was also well cooked with just the right amount of char and still soft and chewy but not soggy. Loved the flavor combination of the special of the day. Unfortunately I don't remember the exact toppings. Salad was also fresh and delicious. Will definitely return to try more.

We ran to this place from Manhattan, lured by the lavish reviews. Space is great, very cool atmosphere. So is the staff, impeccable. Problems started with the wine. We were given a choice of bubbly, white, orange or red. We opted for dry white which came with a heavy sediment. Once mentioned, lovely waitress changed the wines for us which came without sediment. The wine was pedestrian, a trait that cherished all of their wines we realized later on. They are all from small independent producers with organic production. This does not however mean that they have to be amateur wines which taste horrible. I opted for a beer instead. Pizza - we had 2. First one was margherita with added salami. It was good but poor quality olive oil was the overpowering flavor. 2nd pizza was pops with guanciale and it was much better. In the end, not sure it was worth running 13 miles to this joint
Wine prices are a bit unrealistic, 14$ a glass across the board. Oops Ops.
The sour dough crust is good. The sour beer is on point as well.
Excellent pizza, sourdough comes through nicely. Less profound on the calzone but that was very good too
Omg one of my all time favorite restaurants
One of the best places to get pizza in NYC. I have a hard time deciding whether I like Ops or Roberta’s more.
the best pizza in NY period
Good square pizza! Chewy and tasty.
Adorable space and wonderful service. Their menu is delicious and also pretty small (literally refer to photo for scale). Pictured are the margherita and pops pizzas.
Pizza is great .
Great atmosphere and delicious pizza. Try the Bud with Amaro spike for a unique twist on a classic.

Good Neighborhood spot for pizza. Comfortable space ,warm room. The calzone was delicious..the small plate starters were enjoyable.the salad looked delicious as well. The pizza was tasty. The service could use a little help but it is what it is . Enjoyable meal . I'll have to go back and try out another pizza .

Let's preface with this: there are better pizzas in NYC (Norma, Tramonti la pizza and San Matteo are definitely better).  That being said this is very good pizza.  I'm still very disappointed by the margherita with mushroom: the amount of toppings on the pizza is a joke. You're really eating dough with a little bit of other stuff, where the mozzarella and mushrooms are sprinkled as though it was just decorative.  The calzone was far more satisfying with a lot more to eat other than the dough.  The salad was also very fresh and good.  I think given their pizza dough, they have potential to be a significantly better spot. Looks like people aren't as picky as me but maybe they haven't tried the 3 other places I mentioned.
The food was incredible and the staff was very friendly and helpful. Although out of the way, I would definitely recommend Ops to anyone who asked.

Highly recommend the Pops -- which has onions and guanciale. The carbonara disappointed us (egg was very overcooked) and we weren't huge fans of the Juno either. But the square pizza (we added sausage) was also amazing -- a bit crispier than the regular pizzas, and the selection of natural wines is great.
Best pizza in town no doubt! Add great natural wines and your all set
Was pleasantly surprised. Good pizza and wonderful staff. I was happy to see that Ops is gratuity free.
Amazing.

The pizza crust is light and airy and just the tiniest bit tangy. The toppings on the pizza were fresh and delicious and a perfect combo of flavors. And pizza aside - the salad and dessert were also total delights. Try the house salad and whatever dessert is on for the day. The flourless chocolate cake was amazing. The place has a cute reclaimed look and a great vibe, plus wonderful service and a no-tipping policy. Definitely one of New York’s top pizza spots.

Ops was on my pizzas to try list. Finally got the chance to go here tonight. Probably not best nights to pick (friday). There was an hour wait, but they were very accommodating especially with our 5 year old son with us. So lets get to the food!! We ordered the margherita with onions & the square pizza minus the olives, added the onions. So i like the sour dough crust. It is light airy & doesn't feel so heavy. But it can be a lot for people that are not fans of sour dough. The sauce was just ok for me. I've had much better tasting sauce. Cheese was fresh & in good amount. I liked the crust on the square pizza more. It was nice & crispy on the edges. But I dont think it's worth almost double the price of the margherita. Drinks are good. The tip included in the prices is definitely  a nice addition. The service was great btw. The decor is nice & chill & not overly hipsterish (sorry BK I represent Queens!!). Overall good experience. I would definitely recommend people to go there if they are into sour dough.

Pizza Has good flavors. I tried the square pizza, the crust was good, overpriced? Definitely! As for my taste it had too much parmesan which makes it salty. Had better from some places that sell by a slice. And what is up with all that oil on top? Drizzle means a bit not a boat load.  Artichoke aperitif was just oily and without any citrus taste whatsoever, you could compare it to a store bought, actually some store bought I had were so much better, would never order again. The bread was good but again it was floating in oil and got saturated by it. Would I eat again? No. They think just because it’s a yippie neighborhood, they can charge an arm an a leg.  You want real Italian pizza , go to Fornino pizza.
(Translated by Google) Very welcoming, good coffee and almond croissant  (Original) Tres accueillant,  bon café et croissant aux amandes
Maybe the hest pizza I've had.
Wonderful pizza and friendly staff. My favorite
Soft and crunchy dough and fantastic toppings

The pizza is pretty good but they're small and not cheap at all. The crust is pretty good and the chilli oil they have is also pretty good. Draft beer is not served in pint glasses, which should be considered a crime. Part of the relatively higher sticker price is because there is no tipping, which is fine. But the small portions of food and drink are not commensurate with the prices.

Great pizza. No. Exceptional pizza. Crust was smoky, sauce was light, but pungent. Cute tables. Really nice bathroom (kinda random, but you'll see). Friendly, and able staff. Would definitely go again.
Very good pizza. Slightly larger and a normal personal pie but thinner. They have indoor and outdoor seating. Becoming a neighborhood staple
the calzone special was SO good.
Delicious pizza and wine! Personnel less than friendly but worth it for the food and ambiance.
Excellent pizza and more..Get the house soda it's great
Firing on all cylinders here, and also just the best.
Great spot
Simply the best... better than all the rest  This place has it goin on- will be back soon for more dreamy pizza and wine
One of my fav spots for pizza. Seasonal pies, great wines and sides. Everything you need for a perfect date or a small group of friends

I was so hopeful. Since having a life-changing thin crust pizza in Rome, I was so hopeful this would be close. The salad recommended by the server was excellent and a work of art. The $8 draft beer was good but very small. The Margherita pizza we ordered was... meh. The crust wasn't any thinner than any other NY pizza and the center was soggy. It was soggy. Service was great and tip is included. I'll keep looking for a thin crust pizza.

I hesitate to leave a review here because it's so good and I don't want it to get over crowded. But secret's out peeps. This place is amazing and people know it. Come on a dark cold and rainy night and there won't be any lines. Even on crowded nights, you can usually find a seat at the bar.  In short, it's amazing and you should go.
Amazing place for neapolitan pizza. Beyond the great pizza; the location is great, the drink selection is top notch, and the service was superb.

The pizza here is worth hitting up this restaurant. Ordered the square pie, which was absolutely delicious, and also tried their special white pie, which was also quite good. This place also has a pretty good selection of cocktails. Nothing really negative to say. Service and the decore and mood of the place were both great.
Love the ambiance. Very hipster cute. Low quality alcohol.
Very strong pies. Mostly Neapolitan, but there's a vaguely Detroit style square pie that I quite enjoyed. Crust is soft and delicious, and the toppings are quite tasty. Also, excellent service.
Kinda hate to admit it, but it lived up to the hype
Really tasty dough and sauce. Was a big fan!
Best pizza and foods here best service always friendly staff
The pizza was phenomenal, the drinks were amazing. The staff was friendly. I will be back
Cicero - one of the most delicious pizzas in New York City. Different onions depending on the season. The sourdough crust is great, and all the pizzas are excellent or beyond. Great wines too.
Tips included !

Ops is an incredibly thoughtful pizza establishment. The food is always high quality, the staff is very friendly and helpful, and the atmosphere and interior is lovely. It has an edge above comparable pizza restaurants in the taste and charm. The tables are really cute and cozy but I really enjoy sitting at the bar stools and watching them make the pizza. I’d recommend trying one the nightly specials in addition to their staple menu items. Their cocktails are really good and they have an incredibly curated wine list. Tip is included in the price which is a nice additive for the security of the staff and clear transparency for the customer.
Great service, fun wine selection, and the square pizza was delicious!
The Margherita Pizza was sooo good. It left me wanting more!!
Great pizza, beet salad and amazing bread! Nice & friendly staff, highly recommended.
Square slice is one of the best pizzas in NY

It feels kind of strange to say this after living in NYC for 20 years but this is probably the best pizza I've ever had. Better than any pizza literally anywhere in the US or any other country for that matter. I'm not sure how they do it. And I've been to dozens of pizza places in NYC including all the legends. It's just amazing. The decor is really nice. The cocktails are good. Service is solid. Gratuity is included. Prices are fine. My wife, my two friends and I were totally knocked out. Well done.

My favorite brick oven/neopolitan pizza spot in NYC. Soughdough crust and premium ingredients make their pizza standout. Great, affordable natural wines. Only problem would be the use of tomato sauce cans to hold the pizzas instead of legit holders. The possibility of having your pizza hit the floor is a little too high for my taste.

mama mia!  what nice intro to this epicurean heaven.  i had the bean and egg salad. fabulous. it really was. i only wish i could had been explained that what served was exactly what i had ordered.  hints of confusion, for a guy who aims at all good things in life.  #ops  naturally, the smiles made my salad taste the best.  mille grazie!  🏆
Favorite pizza in NYC. Sourdough crust. Natural wines. Great vibes.

Good Neighborhood spot for pizza. Comfortable space ,warm room. The calzone was delicious..the small plate starters were enjoyable.the salad looked delicious as well. The pizza was tasty. The service could use a little help but it is what it is . Enjoyable meal . I'll have to go back and try out another pizza .
Total gem, worth any wait time. Don’t want to get into it but amongst the best puzzas in NY
Yummy pizza, lots of choices, unique cocktails.

I love pizza. I eat pizza several times a week. I'm always looking for the best pizza places in Brooklyn and let me tell you this is one of them. The dough, the flavor, everything was spot on. I highly recommend the one I had, I think it was called "pops" with guanciale and onions.  Also great service and hospitality from the stafd which sadly is a rare think in Brooklyn. The girl that greated us was very nice and attentive as well as our server.  Everything on top of a wonderful vibe. Also I really dig the "no tipping" scheme they have going on. The prices and higher than other places but they are getting the tipping % they rightfully deserve.
Great salads, amazing pizza, especially the square pizza
Great service delicious food.

Pizza is some of the best in North brooklyn and they have a very nice wine selection that's always evolving.  Decour is super cool with tile and built-in wood benches.  If you like Roberta's or Houdini you'll also love this place.
Amazing.. Absolutely amazing
Very poor pizza,never going back

Super super good food, great atmosphere really friendly staff. I'M an out of towner in NYC and they mad me feel right at home. Top quality ingredients good beer. A little spendy but it's an up scale eatery. Worth the mile walk from my rig.

Ops is hands-down my favorite pizza place in NYC. The neopolitan style pies are all great - but I'm partial to the classic margherita and the Juno (with potatoes and broccoli rabe). The calzone special is also always great. I love their wines as well - tell them what you're in the mood for and they'll bring you a few bottles to try, all the same price.
Good pizza.
So delicious. Very well composed flavors. Good atmosphere. Gracious staff. Definitely eat here. Try the Calzone!
Excellent pizza and very nice ambiance!
Ops is our #1 spot in New York! The wine and the pizza will blow your mind 💯💯💯
Natural wine is superb. Dope pizza. But don't pass on the salad. It's the best.

Ops is the best pizza place in Bushwick. Small and intimate, with an extensive wine list and great cocktails. The pizza is authentic Neapolitan style, absolutely delicious and the antipasti and salads are always fresh and amazing.
Best pizza I ever had
Can’t get enough of the potato pizza! Also the wine... it’s perfect. They let you try before you buy, which is a great way to explore new wines! Oh and they have a killer amaro selection.
Great service, awesome pizza. Incredible wine. Over all a very good experience. Best food on out NYC trip so far
Excellent! All of their food is delicious
Such a cozy spot! The grandma pizza is delicious. For wine they ask your preferences and then bring over a few bottles for you try and select. It was a great experience.
The pizza and the calzone were extremely good. The drinks too and our waiter amazing.
Amazing pizza
Good pizza and wine selection
Limited menu but everything is awesome and tips are included, which I love. Excellent wine and Amari too! Also the pizza crust is sourdough so it's low-FODMAP friendly!
Cool wine spot. Good food, great service.
Creative and delicious pizza
Very very good. Let you taste lots of wines to pick your favorite .
Great food
Great food.

After reading a couple of reviews and a big craving for pizza, I decided to try Ops. I had their calzone, nightly special pizza and a seasonal beer. Overall it was tasty, but nothing very special. On the other hand, the service was phenomenal. We were seated outside and he checked up on us periodically (not too much and not too little). The prices is where I thought was too high. For a calzone, Pizza, and three beers, it came out to $71. IMO, I don’t think it was worth it.
So so good. Delicious pizza and great wine selection.
If it were closer to park slope I would eat there three times a week!

Amazing neapolitan style pizza and the other menu items are delicious as well. All natural wine list, quiet intimate setting, out door seating and friendly staff. This place is one of my favorites in brooklyn.
Amazing.  My fave.  Stay away!

Quality of this place has gone down-hill from a couple of years ago. Basically the only ingredient that I tasted in the pizza was onions. Pizza was dry but somehow too oily at the same time? But mostly dry. And small. The good things about OPS is that sometimes the restaurant is empty, so you can enjoy it being quiet. But the servers are more interested in bantering with themselves compared to serving you. I'd give it a miss. For the price, and taste, honestly it's a coin toss of here vs. Dominoes. Better yet, just visit Roberta's, which is consistently good

I really enjoy this place a lot. The pizza is very unconventional with odd toppings that fit together perfectly. This is not an Italian style pizza nor an American one, in fact I love the fact that this place is just its own thing. They use sourdough for both the pizzas and the bread. Besides pizza, they also have a few plates of seasonal vegetables and more which they accompany with the freshest bread. The ambience is very cozy and friendly with a different selection of wine and cocktails. Also, the gratuity is included which I think is a nice touch and a very considerate decision for both patrons and the people who work there.
Amazing pizza! Tip is included in the pricing.

Very good pizza and drinks. Fresh and lovely flavors. The place is a weird setup and doesn't have as much space for patrons and seating as I think they could have. I went with a group of 6 on a Sunday night and we still didn't have to wait very long though (15 minutes)
It’s a pleasant backdrop in bushwick Far away from the noise and clatter With decent pizza I have yet to dine in
Great pizza, chill vibes and good service. Gets busy in the evenings.
Perfect

Great service, relaxed environment and delicious food!  The specials are always good.
One of the best pizzas, in my opinion. They have a great wine, beer and liquor selection too.
Really quality pizza - give it a try
PIZZA is great and delicious, portions aren't really that big but the pies are wonderful.
Excellent. This is really great pizza and worth a visit. Pizza is the real focus and don't waste your time with anything else. I'd recommend at least a pizza per person.

It was aite.  The space seems large if you're lucky enough to not have to sit at the bar, or one of those odd-end tiny tables (which realistically for a pizza and drinks/sides.. Just doesn't work very well. The upside to this is that you may be so squished in that you never get a piece of food on your lap). There doesn't seem to be a lot of seating options for individuals or couples, many big tables meant for 5-8+ people.  The atmosphere is loud! I went with a friend on a weekday afternoon and the place was packed! Must be a bit good sign, he reasoned, though I had my reservations at the door. So we went in, despite not being able to really talk amongst ourselves since the reverberation of everyone else's chatter seems to work against the shape of the room (great though should there intend to be live music). It was almost loud enough to warrant me wanting to leave, but we stayed- most people here tend to come in hordes with their friends, and it's loud group-talk versus loud individual talk - the way two or three people talk amongst themselves en mass is much less amplified than spread out groups.  The prices were a bit up there, though of course anyone living in NYC who's probably gotten a $1 slice, what isn't expensive? ($1 Pizza is the only thing that stayed affordable here- how did it survive the times? We need an author on this phenomena!) We ordered a side of mixed greens which seemed to be collared greens and a handful of beans. It was something like $9, I could have definitely eaten 5 and not have yet felt full.  We then ordered a glass of wine- it was in the double digits below $20 ($12-15 I believe?), which isn't surprising for wine, until we saw it arrived in this itty bitty glass! The wine was nice but the price:liquid amount ratio was quite the 'oh' moment for us. We got the pattern of 'big price tiny serving size' down and prepared for our pizza.  The size of it wasn't terrible, but it was shorter than your average slice - thing of a typical NYC slice, and cut about 2 1/2 inches off from the crust side. That's about the size we were dealing with- something that we didn't feel quite justified the price, especially because it wasn't particularly mind-blowing.  Conclusion: my taste buds and atmosphere affinity are different than yours, so take it as you will. This time was a bust for me, but I'd try it again - so long as I wasn't paying the bill 😉
Great pizza and great service.

Pizzas are delicious. Stay away from the sides, they're weird and unsatisfying. Because of the hispster nature of the place, don't expect silverware, unless you ask for it. As others have remarked, the dough is very good and memorable.
One of the best pizza spots in NYC. The sourdough crust is so unique and good. The great service and the interior is really nice too.  Highly recommend coming here if you're a pizza fan.

Honestly some of the best pizza I’ve ever had. The sourdough crust is light and airy, but with an amazing complex flavor. The wines we sampled were all spectacular, but a special shout-out goes to the sparkling red, which I had never had before. The hostess was a bit brusque, but our server couldn’t have been nicer. Get the Margherita and the Juno if you can.
Good pizza! Nicely decorated & clean. Great service. Our square pizza was sourdough. Be aware of that, it was good just not advertised on menu.

This place is pretty great.  Sourdough pizza and the calzones they often have as a special are spot on.  I also enjoy their approach to wine as you can give them a few words that describe what kind of wine you usually like and they tend to come back with a couple bottles that match that profile.  Overall, highly recommended.

good fancy sit-down pizza. cocktails and draft beer selection are good. tiny tables, only good for parties of three or less. A very good option for late night dining. However, its a popular spot, so menu items and toppings can run out in the later hours.

Wow. Kolsh was delicious. Pizza was delicious. Still surprised that I didn't have to write a tip. Highly recommended place. I want to come back and try the rest of the pizza.  Edit: Had 90% of the pizzas now. Every staff member is incredibly kind with distinct personality. Which you'd think bare minimum is to encourage a tip, but this is a no tip establishment so in reality they're all really this kind and they clearly enjoy their jobs. Which is awesome. This is the best pizza restaurant in NY and I still travel hours to get here.

Wonderful spot with amazing pizza, great service. The sourdough crust is chewy and tasty. I have yet to have a pizza here I didn't love. No tipping here. Come early because it does get crowded and there can be a wait.
One of the best pizza places in Brooklyn. Drinks can be expensive here.

Not having a wine list isn’t cool, it’s just a major bummer. You are forced to try to pick a wine by having a discussion with a server who (although sweet) doesn’t know anything about wine. The wine they have available is good... I saw lots of cool bottles displayed I would have loved to enjoy, but sadly there is really no option to get a chance to drink any of them because there is no list to order from, so you just drink some random bottle, you are not even sure what it is, but you felt obligated to say yes to this bottle that they brought over to you even though you don’t really like it... Because they are terribly busy.... And you are clearly putting this server out by being picky. The pizza might have saved the place, but after waiting 40 min for a pizza (sitting down at a table after ordering waiting, not waiting for a table)  we had to leave to get to a show, so sadly we never got to try it.  I’m just thankful I don’t live in Bushwick so I never have to go back to this pretentious and frustrating place.

Really really good pizza. The pizza that Roberta’s used to make and Speedy Romeo could never attain. Wine program was excellent, and unconventional. Every wine was offered by the glass at very reasonable prices, excellent selection of natural wine. Place was hopping when we got there on a Sunday night but they found us a spot at the bar in short order. Will Return.
Decent
Great pizza so prepare to wait or come early
Best pizzas in Brooklyn! Try the chocolate cake 👌
Cozy , lovely place. Nice music
Delicious Pizza

once i tried this pizza it supplanted my previous #1 (santa panza) and is now my favorite. the crust is simply perfect! i highly recommend the Many Onions pie. unfortunately i did not get a photo of it as it was just scarfed down, but i did snap a shot of the square pie which was also fantastic and worth waiting for. the only con is that they have terrible 'hot chili oil', it is very, very weak.

My friends live right around the corner from this spot and we turned here after Nicandra's was full. The square pie is incredible - make sure you order this pizza! It does take longer to cook so keep that in mind. We also ordered the Juno which was a nice, simple white pie. The sourdough bread is also amazing. We were full with a party of four, but note that it took over two hours from walking in and leaving, and we were seated immediately. The menu prices do include tip.
Pizza is excellent. The natural wine is even better.

The margarita was classic and great, but I could not stop eating the crust of cicero. Solid pies. Somewhat slow service, but still SUCH GREAT SERVICE. She may not know it yet, but the bartender is kind of my best friend.
Amazing pizza in a hip atmosphere. Always interesting and great wine.
Amazing pizza. Cute place and ambience. I got married here so there's a special place in my heart for it and it's covered in cheesy goodness.
Many onions pie = many tears of joy
Yum
A nice descent  and mature place with real organic ingredients on pizzas.looking for vegetables healthy pizzas?dat its ops pizza.
Great wine. No tipping establishment. Recommend the onion 🍕.

Amazing pizza. Ex Estela guys in the kitchen. Daily selection of salads, apps, and pizza, along with staples. Wine rotates often as well. Very reasonably priced for quality of food. Space is mellow and not overcrowded or hectic. That being said, its not very large so there may be a wait during peak times. Miss living around the corner.

Seasonal cocktail was delicious! My boyfriend was a big fan of the "fancy negroni" (a bit more bitter than a normal negroni). The square pie was the bomb, and the perfect size for two fairly hungry folks. We were also tempted by the red wine, and enjoyed being able to taste the options before deciding.
(Translated by Google) Better than Robert  (Original) Better than Robertas
Knowledgeable staff. Solid pizza. Hasn't been overwhelmed with people yet like Roberta's.
oh so delcioso. ⚡
The servers are very knowledgeable about the food and great at drink recommendations. The rotating appetizers are delicious and the pizzas are interesting and tasty.
Top pizza spot in Bushwick.

I was at my very new boyfriends place while he was at work and was looking for the closest sit-down dinner spot. Ops was a block from him so pizza it was. Two stillwater IPAs and a margherita pizza later, I was hooked, and super sad i finished everything so fast. The point is, I'm really glad this absolute gem is so close to his apartment.
Best goddamn pizza in my whole life
This place is magical. Legitimately some of the best pizza I've had paired with some of the craziest wine. The square pie was my personal favorite!
I just wanted you to know that the way you do it is the best way to make it.
10/10 will come again and can't believe how many amazing natural wines we were able to try by the glass. I think we stayed for over 4 hours and found it really hard to leave. Go. Now.

Sour dough pizza was top notch. Fantastic ambience inside. Wines were a little pricey but great deals on draught beer. Appetizers also great. Easily one of the top 10 pizzas in all of New York. absolutely worth the trip

Love the sourdough crust pizza, especially the potato pizza they sometimes have on special. The salads are also very good. The service was a bit slow at first but has gotten much better, and the staff is always friendly (despite this being a non-tipping restaurant--wish more places would pay their staff a living wage!).
Phenomenal pizza and specials, cheap and delicious beers on tap, tip is included in prices.  Hands down a must if you enjoy top notch pizza.
Taste treats!
Pretty great venue for a few drinks.
yummy pizza with laid back staff
Antipasti was fantastic!
Pretty delicious.
So much potential.  Just too fussy.  Special pizzas you can't change and standard pizzas you can add toppings to but not the ones from the specials .. could be great with some small changes.

A bit overpriced in my opinion, but the staff was SO friendly and really accommodating. The food was good but if I'm being honest not the best pizza I've ever had. It was a really cozy spot though, good for a date!

Delicious pizza and thoughtful staff that help you choose from a seasonal menu and rotating offerings of wines by the glass. A must-go for those in Bushwick and Ridgewood. Some might even argue the crust is superior to Roberta's, but really that's for you to decide!

Great Pizza with beer and wine pairings. Cheese plates are well curated. Gratuity is included in menu prices. Overall nice feel and we'll be back again  Update: staff is in the swing of things and this has become a favorite spot in the neighborhood
The best!
Delicious pizza, great wine, great people.
